 may be significant for chiral\nsymmetry breaking. Since the bound states are defined at equal time in all\nframes they have a non-trivial Lorentz covariance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 May 2016 09:01:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-21"}
